.ie n .IP """random_noncentral_f($n, $dfn, $dfd, $nonc)""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWrandom_noncentral_f($n, $dfn, $dfd, $nonc)\fR" 4
.IX Item "random_noncentral_f($n, $dfn, $dfd, $nonc)"
When called in  an array context, returns an  array of  \fR\f(CI$n\fR\fI\fR deviates
generated from the \fInoncentral F\fR  (variance ratio) distribution with
degrees of freedom \fI\fR\f(CI$dfn\fR\fI\fR (numerator)  and \fI\fR\f(CI$dfd\fR\fI\fR (denominator); and
noncentrality parameter \fI\fR\f(CI$nonc\fR\fI\fR.   When  called in a  scalar context,
generates and returns only one such deviate as a scalar, regardless of
the value of \fI\fR\f(CI$n\fR\fI\fR.
.Sp
Argument restrictions:  \fR\f(CI$dfn\fR\fI\fR must  be at least   1, \fI\fR\f(CI$dfd\fR\fI\fR must be
positive, and \fI\fR\f(CI$nonc\fR\fI\fR must be non-negative.
.Sp
There are no defaults; all four arguments must be provided.
.ie n .IP """random_poisson($n, $mu)""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWrandom_poisson($n, $mu)\fR" 4
.IX Item "random_poisson($n, $mu)"
When called  in an array context,  returns an array  of \fR\f(CI$n\fR\fI\fR outcomes
generated  from the \fIPoisson\fR  distribution  with mean  \fI\fR\f(CI$mu\fR\fI\fR.  When
called  in a  scalar   context, generates and  returns  only  one such
outcome as a scalar, regardless of the value of \fI\fR\f(CI$n\fR\fI\fR.
.Sp
Argument restrictions: \fR\f(CI$mu\fR\fI\fR must be non-negative.
.Sp
There are no defaults; both arguments must be provided.
